					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12857110#post-4449526</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12857110/scp-4731#post-4449526</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2019 20:45:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MaliceAforethought</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2902864</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I love everything about this, from the title to the ending line. I love how it ties into stuff without being part of an explicit continuity, I like how it portrays the Foundation's handling of &quot;everyone sees an anomalous event&quot;, and I like how it captures cosmic&#8230; well, not cosmic <em>horror</em>, per se, but certainly cosmic unease. It's got this horrible sense of atmospheric dread to it, and given the lack of anything explicitly horrifying about it, that's extremely impressive.</p> <p>Hard to believe this was coldposted, to be honest. Hard upvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
